top.value: Head of Strategy and Quality Management

The overall objective of the partnership engagement between DanChurchAid and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Denmark is to contribute to achieving the Sustainable Development Goals and the objectives in Denmark's strategy for development cooperation and humanitarian action while simultaneously working towards DCA's international goals: Save Lives, Build Resilient Communities and Fight Extreme Inequality.

1. Suspected Hazardous Areas are surveyed, marked, cancelled and reported for clearance in accordance with National Standards to the benefit of the affected community. 2. Awareness of Explosive Remnants of War and Improvised Explosive Device-related risks for women, men, girls and boys in contaminated areas is increased through Risk Education. 3. Accountability and technical capacities of Humanitarian Mine Action stakeholders are reinforced.
DanChurchAid will conduct mine action activities including clearance, risk education, and victim assistance in South Sudan, Mali, Libya and Lebanon.
DCA will deliver a 12-month intervention to contribute to human security in and around the city of Derna in Libya
DCA will deliver a phased intervention to support the stabilization of Sirte and assist people from the city and surrounding areas with their urgent needs.

• Outcome 1 – Security and stability is enhanced, risk of death or injury to individuals and in communities is enhanced or removed. • Outcome 2 – Enhanced resilience of vulnerable groups through improved access to resources, livelihoods and socio-economic reconstruction.
The report contains overview of DCA global activities and results in 2019
In our updated International Strategy 2019–2022 we focus on strategy indicators for 2018 and on overall strategic decisions made by DCA’s Board and senior management.
The DCA Global and Strategic Results Framework (GRF) has been established as a learning tool aimed at gathering and assessing information on DCA's global performance.
